title: v0.0.5
body: I can't push directly to master :p

title: Rewrite http transport to use latest hyper.
Change the return type used for eth_sign from H512 to H520.
body: Since the signature data consists of "r (32 byte)", "s (32 byte)" and "v (1 byte)", I think that it is correct to receive at H520 instead of H512.

title: Decoding FixedBytes.
body:
Fixes #50

Seems that also `FixedBytes` deserialization was missing.

title: fixed TransactionReceipt fields && added tests for deserialization
body: transaction receipt does not have fields called `index` and `hash` [docs](https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/JSON-RPC#eth_gettransactionreceipt)

title: removed lifetimes
body: had difficulties using `send_transaction_with_confirmation` so I removed lifetimes from `EthFilter::stream`, `wait_for_confirmations` and `send_transaction_with_confirmation`

title: version 0.0.4
body: version `0.0.3` uses very old version of ethabi `0.2`

title: Fix backpressure in IPC transport.
body: Cloning a channel creates a buffer slot for it which could result in unbounded queue if the requests are produced faster than they can be processed.

title: Initial version of batch requests.
body: (Still in progress (need to get rid of Box), but would like you guys to have a look already).

title: fixed filter names
body: Also made `CallResult` field public, cause it is used by many public functions

title: Various small improvements
body:
- Expose `helpers` (makes it simpler to write custom APIs)
- Add `Deref<Target=[u8]>` to uints and `From<&[u8]>` for `Bytes`
- Make `Transport` blanket implementation more generic (covers `Arc` and `Rc`)

title: Will you update the definition of Log?
body:
I would like to use the Log address field.
Thank you.

title: Hyper instead of reqwest.
body: It doesn't support https, but has way less dependencies.

title: Fix for IPC transport
body: In case there are two responses in the buffer (which can happen when you send two requests concurrently) the second one was not parsed at all.

title: Bump Deps, add Ord and From<&[u8]> to uint.
More types: block, transactions, receipt, and log.
